@startuml
actor Lecturer
participant "Crypto Demo Controller" as Controller
participant "Crypto Demo Service" as CryptoService
participant "SecureRandom" as Random
participant "Cipher (AES-GCM)" as Cipher

Lecturer -> Controller : POST /api/crypto-demo/encrypt\nplaintext message
Controller -> CryptoService : encryptMessage(plaintext)
CryptoService -> Random : generate fresh nonce/IV
Random --> CryptoService : nonce
CryptoService -> CryptoService : load/generate demo AES key
CryptoService -> Cipher : init AES-GCM with key + nonce
Cipher --> CryptoService : ready
CryptoService -> Cipher : encrypt plaintext
Cipher --> CryptoService : ciphertext + auth tag
CryptoService --> Controller : nonce + ciphertext package
Controller --> Lecturer : encrypted response

Lecturer -> Controller : POST /api/crypto-demo/decrypt\nnonce + ciphertext package
Controller -> CryptoService : decryptMessage(payload)
CryptoService -> Cipher : init AES-GCM with same key + nonce
Cipher --> CryptoService : ready
CryptoService -> Cipher : decrypt ciphertext
Cipher --> CryptoService : plaintext or auth failure
CryptoService --> Controller : plaintext result or error
Controller --> Lecturer : decrypted plaintext or tamper failure

note right of CryptoService
Pack 05 keeps AES-GCM as a separate artefact demo.
TLS still protects normal API transport in the secure system design.
end note

note right of Random
A fresh nonce/IV must be generated for every encryption.
Nonce reuse with the same key is prohibited.
end note
@enduml

